<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Swenson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have already said to Mr. Brun that I would sign a protocol extending
                            limit ratification whenever he is authorized.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>